### Day 1 Example (What Customer Receives)

**6:00 AM:**
> Morning Jamie 🌺 
> 
> Meet Baxter where he is today. Today's drill: The Calm Reset (15 min)
> 
> Before we fix the reactivity, we need a dog who can THINK. Pick a quiet spot. Wait for Baxter to naturally calm down, look at you, relax his body. Mark that moment with a soft "good" and gentle touch. 
> 
> Do 3 rounds of 5 min each. Don't rush it. 
> 
> Video demo: [link] 
> 
> Reply DONE when complete. Questions welcome anytime — I check messages twice daily.
> 
> — Unkle

**8:30 PM (if they reply "Done"):**
> Nice work. Tomorrow: The Pattern Interrupt (how to stop the spiral before it starts). Sleep well 🐕

**If they reply with question:**
> "He kept getting up during the calm periods"

**Matthew's response (AI-assisted, sent within 4-6 hours):**
> Totally normal. Baxter's been amped up for a while — his nervous system needs time to recalibrate. When he gets up, don't say anything. Just wait. No eye contact, no command. Boredom becomes the only option. He'll come back. Patience wins here. — Unkle

